Novorossiisk closed by threat of thunderstorm . Oil loadings at the Russian port of Novorossiisk were suspended on Tuesday after a thunderstorm warning , shipping sources said . The Black Sea port , which is the main outlet for Russian Urals crude exports , was closed at 0930 local time . A fairly strong southerly wind was blowing and the swell reached 1 . 2 metres , the source said . The 145 , 000 tonne Sea Princess crude tanker sailed before the suspension was put in place , but the 80 , 000 tonne Prosperity and the 63 , 000 tonne Seawind 2 were both at berth . - - London Newsroom + 44 171 542 5387 
